I'm not entirely sure why and I couldn't find any references, but the following code fails to redirect to https on request for the root path (http://mydomain.com).


    app.UseHttpsRedirection();
    app.UseMvc();
    // map all SPA (clinet side) requests to a catch-all
    // via: https://weblog.west-wind.com/posts/2017/Aug/07/Handling-HTML5-Client-Route-Fallbacks-in-ASPNET-Core
    app.Run(async (context) => {
        context.Response.ContentType = "text/html";
        var rootHomepage = Path.Combine(env.WebRootPath, "index.html");
        // deliver the default index.html of the frontend
        if (File.Exists(rootHomepage))
            await context.Response.SendFileAsync(rootHomepage);
        else
            await context.Response.WriteAsync($@"<html><body><h1>No homepage configured called index.html</h1></body></html>");
        });

It works fine locally on kestrel, but on my development server - also using Kestrel - it's only working on requests that aren't to the root path. With the root path requests are delivered via http and no redirect takes place. Any ideas?

